---
import ElevationLayout from '../../layouts/ElevationLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/elevation/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/elevation/Section.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';
import { productJsonLd } from '../../lib/structured-data';

const product = getProductBySlug('governance-templates-guided')!;
const jsonLd = productJsonLd(product, 'https://evoked.dev/products/governance-templates-guided');
---

<ElevationLayout
  title="Agent Governance Templates (Guided)"
  description="Five governance templates with worked examples from a real system. $5 PDF."
  structuredData={jsonLd}
>
  <Hero
    eyebrowParts={["Products", "Implementation kit"]}
    headline="The templates, filled in."
    metaphor={["Five templates. Worked examples."]}
    sub="Common mistakes and completion checklists, drawn from a real 142-agent system in operation."
  />

  <Section marker="FIG · I" heading="Why guided">
    <p class="lede">
      The free templates tell you what to write. These show you how it looks
      when it's done - with examples from a real 142-agent system that has been
      operating under governance since December 2025.
    </p>
    <p class="pd-body">
      Each template includes a filled-in example, a "common mistakes" callout,
      and a completion checklist so you know when you're done.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · II" heading="The five templates">
    <div class="pd-pillars">
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">1</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Agent charter</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">Who is this agent? What is it for? What are its boundaries? The charter is the identity document your agent needs before it does anything else.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">2</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Restraint specification</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">What must this agent refuse to do? Six refusal categories with examples. The specification that defines the edges your agent will not cross.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">3</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Memory schema</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">What does this agent remember? What does it forget? Who decides? The schema that governs your agent's persistence.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">4</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Deliberation framework</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">How do your agents disagree? How are conflicts resolved? The framework for productive disagreement in multi-agent systems.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">5</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Drift monitoring</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">How do you know when an agent has changed? Behavioral baselines, measurement cadence, and escalation thresholds.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · III" heading="Who this is for">
    <div class="pd-audience">
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Developers who learn by example</h3>
        <p>The blank template is free. The filled-in version with commentary costs $5. If you learn better from seeing how it's done, this is for you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Teams starting governance</h3>
        <p>Hand the guided templates to your team. Each one has a completion checklist. When all five are checked off, run the scan and verify.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Compliance-minded builders</h3>
        <p>The EU AI Act's use-based high-risk obligations take effect 2 December 2027 (revised from 2 August 2026 under the May 2026 Digital Omnibus; provisional political agreement pending Official Journal publication). Article 5 prohibitions and General-Purpose AI rules are live today. These templates map directly to governance requirements in Articles 14, 50, and 72.</p>
        <p class="pd-audience-fineprint"><em>Regulatory facts verified 2026-06-06.</em></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · IV" heading="Buy the templates">
    <div class="pd-purchase">
      <div class="pd-price">$5</div>
      <p class="pd-purchase-lead">PDF download. Five templates with worked examples and checklists.</p>
      <a
        href={product.stripePaymentLink}
        class="pd-buy-cta"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
      >Get the Templates</a>
      <p class="pd-purchase-fineprint">
        Want to see the framework first? Check our free
        <a href="https://github.com/lowkey-divine/agent-governance-starter-kit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">governance starter kit</a>
        on GitHub.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="NOTA · BENE" heading="Go deeper" closing={true}>
    <p class="lede">
      The templates give you the structure. If you want the full implementation
      walkthrough, two doorways from here.
    </p>
    <div class="pd-upsell">
      <a href="/products/governance-implementation-guide" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>Implementation Guide ($9.99)</h3>
        <p>Step-by-step governance implementation for CrewAI, LangGraph, and Pydantic AI. 25 pages of framework-specific guidance.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">View guide &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/products/agent-governance-starter-kit" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>Agent Governance Starter Kit ($49)</h3>
        <p>The complete governance framework - charter, boundaries, drift thresholds, accountability protocols, and authority structures.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">View starter kit &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</ElevationLayout>

<style>
  /* Page-local: card-level fineprint for the verified-on date stamp
     inside the compliance-minded audience card. */
  .pd-audience-fineprint {
    font-size: 0.78rem !important;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet) !important;
    margin-top: 0.5rem !important;
  }
  .pd-purchase-fineprint a {
    color: var(--el-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--el-rule);
  }
  .pd-purchase-fineprint a:hover {
    color: var(--el-text);
    border-color: var(--el-accent);
  }
</style>
